author: gtully
msg: revert http://fisheye6.atlassian.com/changelog/activemq/?cs=958009 - concurrent dispatch with transaction completion breaks when the cache is disabled, either through memory limit or through durable subs with existing messages in the store. cannot see the use case though as the transaction semantic is broken if a message can get dispatched but a commit can still fail. With dispatch ocurring postCommit like before, the option for kahaDB to do concurrent transaction dispatch is disabled
